Register with redhat and get 60 days free trail for AAP Latest version and download tar.gz file
Create redhat (latest) instance  m4.large and storage of 50GB and allow inbound 80 and 443 TCP connections
Open cmd and go where tar file exists (cd downloads)
Copy the .tar.gz in server and gunzip and later untar the file
make changes in inventory 
[automationcontroller]
hostname ansible_connection=local 
add "admin password" and "pg password"in file

run ./setup.sh

1using https://ip we can open tower (using the creds which we have set in inventory file)

when opening tower using ip, subscription management will come and there we should give redhat portal username and password
later subscription will populate, should select and click on next next.
done	
